---
const principles = [
  {
    n: '01',
    title: 'Native by default.',
    body:
      'The platform is not an obstacle to route around with a browser engine. It is the medium. When the experience is the product, I build on Win2D, Direct2D and D3D directly — and accept the cost of doing so, because the result is something a web shell can’t reach.',
  },
  {
    n: '02',
    title: 'Build the hard part yourself.',
    body:
      'Piece tables, red-black trees, a streaming markdown layout engine, an ISO 32000 PDF renderer, a Sugiyama diagram layout — written by hand when the default abstraction couldn’t deliver the UX. The hard part is usually the whole point.',
  },
  {
    n: '03',
    title: 'Performance is a budget.',
    body:
      'Frame time and allocation count are requirements, not aspirations. Hot paths are zero-allocation, buffers are pooled, draw calls are counted. A tile cache that went from 127 ms to 0.2 ms wasn’t luck — it was a number someone decided to own.',
  },
  {
    n: '04',
    title: 'Spec first, then phases, then gates.',
    body:
      'Every project starts as a written spec. Execution runs in reviewable phases with hard review gates between them. The discipline isn’t bureaucracy — it’s what lets the ambitious version actually ship.',
  },
];
---

<section id="approach" class="section approach">
  <div class="wrap approach__inner">
    <header class="approach__head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Approach</p>
      <h2 class="approach__title">How I build.</h2>
    </header>

    <ol class="approach__list" role="list">
      {principles.map((p) => (
        <li class="principle">
          <span class="principle__n mono" aria-hidden="true">{p.n}</span>
          <div class="principle__text">
            <h3 class="principle__title">{p.title}</h3>
            <p class="principle__body">{p.body}</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .approach__inner {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(var(--space-6), 6vw, var(--space-9));
  }
  .approach__title {
    font-size: var(--step-4);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }
  .approach__list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
  }
  .principle {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: clamp(var(--space-4), 4vw, var(--space-8));
    padding-block: clamp(var(--space-5), 4vw, var(--space-7));
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }
  .principle:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }
  .principle__n {
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    color: var(--ink-3);
    font-weight: 500;
    padding-top: 0.35em;
  }
  .principle__title {
    font-size: var(--step-3);
    font-weight: 420;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .principle__body {
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .approach__inner {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(220px, 0.4fr) 1fr;
      align-items: start;
    }
    .approach__head {
      position: sticky;
      top: 96px;
    }
  }
</style>
